spec: as3421
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 675 (as3421): __hash__, __eq__, __lt__ dict-presence checks for asyncio types."
    - "Theme: __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ dict-presence (hash(x), x==y, x<y)."
    - "All values False — asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives that do not define __hash__, __eq__, or __lt__ in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__hash__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __hash__. hash() delegates to __hash__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types do not define __hash__ in their own __dict__ — hashing of asyncio synchronization primitives and task/future handles is not a supported pattern. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles with no custom __hash__ in their own __dict__; hash falls back to the inherited id-based hash from object. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: boolean-state and permit-count guards with no __hash__ defined at the class level. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __hash__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__eq__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __eq__. == delegates to __eq__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types do not define __eq__ in their own __dict__; equality comparison falls back to inherited identity comparison from object. asyncio.Task/Future: these types have distinct identities per coroutine and loop; no value-based equality is defined in their own __dict__. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization guards with no __eq__ defined in their own __dict__. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __eq__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__lt__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __lt__. < delegates to __lt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types define no ordering protocol in their own __dict__. asyncio.PriorityQueue sorts its items, but the queue itself has no __lt__ in its __dict__ — comparison applies to the items stored, not the queue object. asyncio.Task/Future/Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore/Queue/LifoQueue: none define __lt__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 675 (__hash__/__eq__/__lt__) — twenty consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 668 (as3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 670 (as3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 671 (as3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 672 (as3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 673 (as3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 674 (as3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 675 (as3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __hash__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__hash__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __hash__.
# hash() delegates to __hash__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types do not define __hash__ in their own __dict__; hashing falls
#   back to the inherited id-based hash from object.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles with no custom __hash__
#   defined in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards with
#   no __hash__ in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-count guards with no __hash__
#   defined at the class level in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __hash__ in
#   their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

