# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __eq__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__eq__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __eq__.
# == delegates to __eq__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types do not define __eq__ in their own __dict__; equality falls
#   back to inherited identity comparison from object.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles compared by identity, not
#   value; no __eq__ defined in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: synchronization guards with no __eq__
#   in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-count guards with no __eq__
#   defined at the class level in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __eq__ in
#   their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

