# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __lt__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__lt__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __lt__.
# < delegates to __lt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types define no ordering protocol in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.PriorityQueue: sorts its queued items by priority, but the queue
#   object itself has no __lt__ in its own __dict__ — item ordering applies
#   to the stored items, not the queue instance.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles with no ordering defined
#   in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization
#   guards with no __lt__ in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __lt__ defined at the class
#   level in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

